init_text:
Is Listening to a Book Just as Good as Reading It?

Do you listen to audiobooks? What are the benefits, in your opinion, of listening instead of reading? Are there advantages to reading that cannot be gained by listening? Which method do you prefer? Why?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: listening to an audiobook is like looking at a painting without ever seeing it in person.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: This is not to say that audiobooks are inferior.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Have you ever listened to an audiobook?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The experience is still valid for sure.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: This way I can listen to the story when doing something else.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Don't get me wrong, I'm not saying that audiobooks are bad, I'm just giving insight as to how I look at them

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: keep in the back of your mind that there is more than one way to read.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I would recommend listening to audiobooks if you're in a car or doing something else that requires your attention outside of just the book
